1
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:34,910
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:37,820
[Episode 8]

3
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,120
Xiaoman.

4
00:01:43,509 --> 00:01:45,710
Xiaoman, come out. I need to talk to you.

5
00:01:45,810 --> 00:01:46,370
Xiaodan.

6
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,259
Are you home...

7
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:48,880
What's up?

8
00:01:49,450 --> 00:01:50,450
Where are you?

9
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,350
Over here.

10
00:01:55,070 --> 00:01:56,600
What are you doing up there?

11
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:59,220
Hurry up. I need to
discuss something with you.

12
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:01,220
I'm watering the neighbor's field.

13
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,870
You know I want to go to Beijing

14
00:02:04,870 --> 00:02:06,840
to enter that hosting competition, right?

15
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,430
But after that mock exam incident,

16
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:10,030
my dad completely forbade me from going.

17
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:10,960
What should I do?

18
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,430
That's tough.

19
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:17,190
But, Zhuang Sen once said,

20
00:02:17,630 --> 00:02:19,560
"Never give up on your dreams."

21
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:20,560
Right?

22
00:02:20,590 --> 00:02:21,860
Yeah, that's what I think.

23
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,520
I don't want to give up either.

24
00:02:23,870 --> 00:02:25,400
Convincing your dad

25
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:28,120
will be difficult.

26
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:30,840
But you know,

27
00:02:31,470 --> 00:02:33,470
on the road to success,

28
00:02:33,710 --> 00:02:35,910
there are countless stumbling blocks.

29
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,520
My dad is only the second one.

30
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:39,710
Your dad is the second one?

31
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,400
Oh my God.

32
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,860
Then what's the first one?

33
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:50,079
Money.

34
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:52,380
I have no money.

35
00:02:52,410 --> 00:02:53,030
What should I do?

36
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:54,120
I'll work with you?

37
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:55,920
But what can I do?

38
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:58,430
Money.

39
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,030
What do you think?

40
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:17,910
So much money?

41
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:19,310
Of course.

42
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,870
Where did you get the money?

43
00:03:22,329 --> 00:03:24,680
I get subsidies
from the factory every day,

44
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,280
and I do so much work.

45
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:28,410
Of course I can save this much.

46
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,760
Isn't Mr. Ding keeping your money for you?

47
00:03:33,190 --> 00:03:35,450
Didn't you say you were
going to Beijing long ago?

48
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:37,579
Right? You need money wherever you go.

49
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,100
I've saved it up for you
for quite a while.

50
00:03:45,050 --> 00:03:47,250
It wasn't easy for you to save this much.

51
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:48,630
And you're giving it all to me?

52
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:49,680
Just take it.

53
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,680
What do I need it for?

54
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,680
I have food, drink,
and a place to stay here.

55
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,680
There's nowhere to spend it anyway.

56
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,360
Besides, I saved this money

57
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,680
just to invest in your dream.

58
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,640
Why are you so good to me?

59
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,400
Don't just invest in me.

60
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:10,560
Invest in yourself too.

61
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,960
What do you want to do in the future?

62
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,150
What do I want to do?

63
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,930
I'm fine with anything.

64
00:04:20,190 --> 00:04:22,390
I have my ways of making money, right?

65
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,390
No need to invest in me.

66
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,190
It's all for you.

67
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:26,000
I'll be a full-time earner from now on,

68
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,400
investing in your dream.

69
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,630
Okay. Then from now on,

70
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,920
I'll be with you whatever you do.

71
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,390
Really?

72
00:04:33,510 --> 00:04:34,190
Really.

73
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,390
Then help me water the field first.

74
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:41,680
I'll count the money for you first.

75
00:04:42,430 --> 00:04:43,190
Over 300.

76
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:44,630
Over 300?

77
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,640
When do you want to leave?

78
00:04:48,159 --> 00:04:49,240
In about a month.

79
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:50,430
Over a month?

80
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,510
Don't worry. It'll definitely be enough.

81
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:54,430
By then, the stack will be much thicker.

82
00:04:54,430 --> 00:04:55,190
Really?

83
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:57,159
Definitely enough for you to go.

84
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:02,330
Take your time counting.

85
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:05,240
I'll take this, then.

86
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,970
Take it. Don't leave any for me.

87
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:07,900
Take it all.

88
00:05:11,630 --> 00:05:14,750
Director, I have an urgent page from home.

89
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,100
Can I borrow your mobile phone?

90
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:16,490
Sure.

91
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,680
Thank you, Director.

92
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:19,240
Thanks.

93
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:25,350
He's calling.

94
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:29,840
Xiaoman.

95
00:05:29,950 --> 00:05:30,600
Sen.

96
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,040
It's Xia Lei.

97
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,490
Lei is there too?

98
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,600
Xiaoman is at my place.

99
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,200
How are you doing in Beijing?

100
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:38,120
Pretty good.

101
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,460
I just finished shooting a scene.

102
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:42,190
The director was afraid I'd delay things,

103
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:44,830
so he lent me his mobile phone.

104
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:47,950
You're on such good terms
with the director now?

105
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:48,830
You bet.

106
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,970
Right. Why did you page me?

107
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:52,830
Right. Well,

108
00:05:53,430 --> 00:05:54,950
didn't I tell you before?

109
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,480
Xiaodan is going to Beijing for that

110
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:58,600
hosting competition.

111
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,510
Do you remember?

112
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:01,840
Come on. I'll find a professional for you.

113
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:04,920
My god, look at you now.

114
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,160
You even know hosts.

115
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,190
Let me tell you something.

116
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,800
Broadcasting and acting
are part of the same family.

117
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,140
Once you get guidance
from a professional,

118
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:13,950
your level improves immediately.

119
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:16,480
Then I'm counting on you for this.

120
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:19,720
Xiaodan and I will get ready at home.

121
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,920
You hurry up and contact your friends.

122
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,510
We'll come to you when we get there.

123
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,170
No problem.

124
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:26,950
By the way, when will you buy a pager?

125
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:28,580
It's easier to keep in touch.

126
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:29,360
That thing is so expensive.

127
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,420
Why would I need it?

128
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,950
Buy a second-hand one.

129
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:34,000
It won't cost much. Don't be so stingy.

130
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,070
I'll go check it out someday.

131
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:36,950
Extra A!

132
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:39,400
The director is calling me.

133
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,000
I can't talk anymore.

134
00:06:41,159 --> 00:06:42,310
They're calling the actors.

135
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,310
When they go to Beijing,

136
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,360
I'm counting on you, Sen.

137
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,890
It's been 59 seconds.
Stop asking for favors.

138
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:52,120
Okay, got it.

139
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:52,870
Over here.

140
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:58,750
Sir.

141
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,800
Let me see. This one.

142
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,490
Where is the screen?

143
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:08,910
-Buy one like this.
-Sir.

144
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,670
Let me take a look at this.

145
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,860
This screen is big.

146
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,310
This looks okay.

147
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:17,790
This one looks good.

148
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,560
Bro, you've been looking for ages.

149
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,360
Are you buying a numeric
or a Chinese display pager?

150
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,360
How much is the numeric one?

151
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,000
How much is the Chinese display one?

152
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,200
Numeric is 300. Chinese display is 600.

153
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:29,360
The Chinese display one
is so much more expensive.

154
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,800
It's not expensive, I'm telling you.

155
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,190
A new one is over a thousand.

156
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:33,430
Do you know why? Because it's second-hand,

157
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,600
that's why it's cheap.

158
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,540
But let me tell you,

159
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:36,940
it works perfectly fine.

160
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,310
Six hundred? Isn't that a bit pricey?

161
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:40,600
Yeah, six hundred is too much.

162
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,930
You get what you pay for.

163
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:45,240
Well, let me... let me think about it.

164
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,430
Don't overthink it, bro.

165
00:07:46,430 --> 00:07:48,640
Listen to me,
just buy this Chinese display pager.

166
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:49,840
Clip it to your waist,

167
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,510
and you'll look real sharp on the street.

168
00:07:51,510 --> 00:07:52,120
Really?

169
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:53,750
Gotta have
the Chinese display pager, right?

170
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:54,510
Right.

171
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,310
Let's get the Chinese display pager.

172
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,250
Go for the big Chinese display pager.

173
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,159
Get a Chinese display pager.

174
00:07:59,159 --> 00:08:00,650
If I don't end up with
a Chinese display pager after all this,

175
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:01,650
what's the point?

176
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,510
Six hundred?

177
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:06,560
One hundred.

178
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:12,070
Two, three, four hundred.

179
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:13,560
Five-ten, five-twenty,

180
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,560
five-thirty, five-forty.

181
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,890
Five-fifty, five-sixty, five-seventy.

182
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:18,750
Five-eighty.

183
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:20,800
Exactly right.

184
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:22,430
Bro,

185
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,950
help me break this 50.

186
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:25,870
What's wrong?

187
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:27,320
It's a bit old.

188
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:28,870
How is this old?

189
00:08:28,870 --> 00:08:30,680
So what if it's old?
You can still spend it.

190
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,540
Look how new it is.

191
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,539
Stop pretending.

192
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,919
Don't understand me?

193
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:36,240
This... this is fake.

194
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:38,260
What's fake?

195
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,169
How can you tell?

196
00:08:41,169 --> 00:08:42,760
Is... is this really fake?

197
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:48,790
Boss.

198
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:49,750
Xiaoman, you're here.

199
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:50,480
Well...

200
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,530
I got paid here a couple of days ago,

201
00:08:54,910 --> 00:08:57,240
and there was
a fake fifty-yuan bill in it.

202
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,550
Impossible.

203
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,290
Impossible.

204
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:01,200
Look at it.

205
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,730
I don't need to look.

206
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,400
I withdrew the money from the bank.

207
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,600
What,

208
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:08,670
you think the bank can give me fake money?

209
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:09,790
Besides,

210
00:09:09,790 --> 00:09:11,840
it's been days since payday.

211
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,290
You come running to me today saying

212
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:15,890
you have a counterfeit bill.

213
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:18,390
How do I know where that money...

214
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,670
-...came from?
-Wait. What do you mean?

215
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:21,340
What, you think I picked up
this fake money

216
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:22,410
to come and exchange it with you?

217
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:24,070
Exactly. I run such a big shop.

218
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,200
Would I give you fake money?

219
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,000
No matter how big your business is,

220
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,000
the money is fake. It's right here.

221
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,440
Where this counterfeit bill came from

222
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:31,140
isn't something that can be
explained just by talking.

223
00:09:31,140 --> 00:09:32,690
You work here for us.

224
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:33,750
Between us,

225
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:36,080
shouldn't there be basic trust?

226
00:09:36,550 --> 00:09:38,790
I could exchange this 50 yuan for you.

227
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:39,960
But think about it.

228
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,620
Do you still want to work here?

229
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,120
When we see each other again,

230
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:46,030
will there be hard feelings between us?

231
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:47,000
What hard feelings?

232
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:49,200
If you replace the money,
I won't have any hard feelings.

233
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,960
That's not how it works.

234
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,390
Look, who hasn't received
counterfeit money these days?

235
00:09:54,390 --> 00:09:55,840
If everyone keeps thinking,

236
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,050
"Where did I get this fake money?"

237
00:09:57,050 --> 00:09:58,510
"What should I do with it?"

238
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,440
Then forget it.
Nothing would ever get done.

239
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,170
Wait, what do you mean?

240
00:10:01,170 --> 00:10:03,630
You're just not going
to replace it, are you?

241
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:08,920
Fine. I'll take the loss.

242
00:10:09,420 --> 00:10:10,600
-It’s on me.
-Xiaoman.

243
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,390
Have some water.

244
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:11,920
Xiaoman.

245
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:12,890
Xiaoman.

246
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,320
What are you up to?

247
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,670
Still fussing over that fake money?

248
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:31,150
I'm reminding myself.

249
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:33,200
To stay on guard.

250
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,250
The gas station gave me fake money.

251
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:40,510
How many gas canisters do I have to change

252
00:10:40,510 --> 00:10:41,960
to earn 50 yuan?

253
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,600
That boss is really heartless.

254
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:49,960
My mom sent this for you.

255
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:52,350
-What is it?
-It’s ginseng bee magma.

256
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,240
Auntie is the best.

257
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:59,270
She always thinks of me
when there's something good.

258
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:00,200
My mom said

259
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:02,080
it's rich in

260
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,360
over 20 vitamins and minerals.

261
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,240
She said hauling gas canisters

262
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:06,930
is exhausting,

263
00:11:06,930 --> 00:11:09,310
so drink this every day
to boost your health.

264
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:11,320
Thank your mom for me when you go home.

265
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,720
This is good stuff.

266
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,080
My mom also said...

267
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:18,080
She wants you to take this cardboard,

268
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:20,630
cut it up, and put it on your cart.

269
00:11:20,790 --> 00:11:22,440
If anyone asks,

270
00:11:22,670 --> 00:11:23,550
"What's this about?"

271
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,890
you say our family sells it.

272
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:26,350
That way, we can sell some.

273
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,270
This looks expensive.

274
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:30,540
You want me to stick it on my tricycle?

275
00:11:30,670 --> 00:11:31,550
You never know.

276
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:32,620
You go through streets
and alleys every day.

277
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:33,740
You meet a lot of people.

278
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:34,520
They'll see it.

279
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,790
"Xiaoman, what is this?"

280
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:36,740
"Ginseng Royal Jelly?"

281
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:38,070
"What's this about?"

282
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,390
"It's from Xia Lei's family."

283
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,080
"Go check out Xia Lei's place."

284
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,360
See? It's promoted.

285
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:44,030
I'm fine with it,
as long as you don't mind.

286
00:11:44,030 --> 00:11:44,790
I don't mind.

287
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:47,210
It'll be conspicuous on your cart, right?

288
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:47,720
Sure.

289
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,770
Let's see what this is.

290
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:54,510
Auntie.

291
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:56,440
Are you cooking?

292
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,480
Have a seat.

293
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:59,780
Xia Lei gave me this royal jelly.

294
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,970
I brought it for you. It's really good.

295
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Why are you acting like a stranger,

296
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:03,930
bringing gifts?

297
00:12:04,030 --> 00:12:04,720
Sit down.

298
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,550
I read the label.

299
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:08,000
It has ginseng and vitamins.

300
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:09,360
It has everything in it.

301
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:10,630
Don't do this again.

302
00:12:10,660 --> 00:12:11,260
Okay.

303
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,030
Guoqiang isn't back yet.

304
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:16,960
Let's eat first.

305
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:18,690
I stewed some beef.

306
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:21,320
How is it?

307
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:22,640
Smells great.

308
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:23,630
Does it?

309
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:24,960
You stewed such a big pot.

310
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,270
It must have taken all morning.

311
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,980
Exactly. Usually, it's faster than this.

312
00:12:27,980 --> 00:12:29,310
The flame is weak today.

313
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,300
Is it out of gas?

314
00:12:31,790 --> 00:12:32,790
Let me take a look.

315
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,680
It's okay. It's still got plenty of gas.

316
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,620
It's not working well.

317
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:43,200
Right?

318
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,600
Anyway, when I shake it,

319
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,960
it always sounds like water.

320
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,080
Yeah, I see.

321
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:49,270
It's been used for too long,

322
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:51,030
so the gas inside isn't burning well.

323
00:12:51,030 --> 00:12:51,670
It needs to be emptied.

324
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:52,900
Get a new tank and it'll be fine.

325
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,080
Can this be poured out?

326
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,670
Yes. I do this every day.

327
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:57,240
I'll pour the water out in a bit.

328
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,470
I'll get a new one.

329
00:12:58,490 --> 00:12:59,360
It will be better when I come back.

330
00:12:59,360 --> 00:12:59,960
All right.

331
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,080
Come chase me.

332
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,170
You're dead.

333
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,660
Don't run up there.

334
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,610
You just had to crowd me now.

335
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:08,080
Hurry! Go away!

336
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,080
Don't run!

337
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,270
Hello, Mr. Ding.

338
00:13:14,270 --> 00:13:15,000
Hello.

339
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:17,630
Call me Big Uncle.
I'm older than your dad.

340
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,000
Picking flowers? Or chili peppers?

341
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,860
Chili peppers.

342
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:21,200
Mr. Ding, you're back!

343
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,060
Big Uncle Ding.

344
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,080
Right, Big Uncle.

345
00:13:24,550 --> 00:13:26,350
Where did you buy the scallions?

346
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:30,390
That smell...

347
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:34,320
Go inside.

348
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,200
What's wrong, Mr. Ding?

349
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,140
What are you doing?

350
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,060
What's the matter?

351
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:45,080
What on earth are you doing?

352
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:47,440
There's leftover gas
in this tank. It's hard to light.

353
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,210
I want to pour it out and get it refilled.

354
00:13:49,210 --> 00:13:50,000
If a cigarette butt falls,

355
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,200
we'll both go flying.

356
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:52,730
Not a single person will be left standing.

357
00:13:52,730 --> 00:13:53,210
No way.

358
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,240
That gas... none of it is flammable.

359
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,080
It smells so strong. Smell it.

360
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,880
You think this won't catch fire?

361
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:58,670
Can it?

362
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:02,670
Then... what should I do?

363
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:04,070
How do I empty this thing?

364
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,510
Did you ever play with mud
and pee when you were a kid?

365
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:10,370
Well, but I... I didn't do it much.

366
00:14:10,430 --> 00:14:12,030
Go upstairs and get a shovel.

367
00:14:12,270 --> 00:14:13,810
We need to take the soil
soaked with this liquid,

368
00:14:13,810 --> 00:14:15,070
dig a hole, and bury it.

369
00:14:16,070 --> 00:14:17,440
Okay. Just a shovel, right?

370
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:17,990
Yeah.

371
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:24,250
Mr. Ding.

372
00:14:24,550 --> 00:14:27,200
You pee first. I just went to
the bathroom at home.

373
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,480
When you guys played
with mud and pee as kids,

374
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,610
did you use real pee?

375
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:32,720
Didn't you use real pee?

376
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:35,400
We used real pee too.

377
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:36,070
Okay.

378
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:39,200
Xiaobo.

379
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:40,840
Going to swap the gas tank?

380
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,390
Yeah.

381
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:43,720
Since my tank has residual liquid,

382
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:45,600
take it to the gas station for me

383
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:47,130
and have them dispose of it.

384
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,390
Just dump the residue in the river.

385
00:14:49,390 --> 00:14:50,320
I wouldn't dare.

386
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:51,800
Won't that cause trouble?

387
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,450
You wouldn't dare?

388
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:55,790
Did you forget
what you did to me in school?

389
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:56,380
Hurry up.

390
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,120
Come on. Help me get this up.

391
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:58,580
Come on.

392
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:04,890
We're loading all of these, right?

393
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,080
Put it there. I don't need your help.

394
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,840
Hurry up. It's really heavy.

395
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,080
Xiaobo,

396
00:15:19,790 --> 00:15:21,910
this can is lighter than normal cans.

397
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,100
Of course it's light,
because there're no residuals.

398
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:26,200
It's not about the residue.

399
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,390
I deliver canisters every day.

400
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:29,480
This is several pounds
lighter than normal.

401
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,700
Weigh it if you don't believe me. It is.

402
00:15:32,110 --> 00:15:33,570
I don't have time for this.

403
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:35,270
Go do whatever you need to do.

404
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,540
Then when will you be back?
I'll wait for you.

405
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:41,150
In a hurry?

406
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,240
They're waiting for it at home.

407
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,500
There's a spare tank inside. Come on.

408
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:48,650
What's going on today?

409
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:54,790
Take it. Just swap it back
before I return this afternoon.

410
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:56,440
Okay. I'm taking it then.

411
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,030
Go ahead.

412
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:57,840
Thanks.

413
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:03,320
Uncle.

414
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:05,270
He might have got suspicious.

415
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:06,670
So what if he has?

416
00:16:06,790 --> 00:16:07,910
It has nothing to do with him.

417
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:09,790
Move away. Let me see what's happening.

418
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:11,160
Everyone steals from the public pot.

419
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:12,890
You'd be a fool not to. Let's go.

420
00:16:21,870 --> 00:16:22,440
Xiaoman,

421
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:27,200
here are your wages for the week.

422
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:27,630
Okay.

423
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:32,240
Isn't this an extra hundred?

424
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:34,840
No, it's not. You know what happened?

425
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,440
I went to the bank a couple of days ago
to withdraw money,

426
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,100
and found a counterfeit bill.

427
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:40,720
I was thinking,

428
00:16:41,030 --> 00:16:42,750
that fake 50 you got last time,

429
00:16:43,030 --> 00:16:44,630
maybe I was the one who gave it to you.

430
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:45,480
Look.

431
00:16:47,310 --> 00:16:48,550
Won't there be a problem?

432
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,150
It's fine.

433
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,670
Even banks have fake bills.

434
00:16:50,670 --> 00:16:52,670
It's okay. No need. 50 is enough.

435
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:55,240
No, you take it all.

436
00:16:55,270 --> 00:16:56,440
You're young.

437
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,550
You're growing.

438
00:16:57,570 --> 00:16:59,200
Buy yourself something good to eat.

439
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,860
Really, it's fine. 50 is fine.

440
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,840
Just take it.

441
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:04,730
We all earn hard money.

442
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:06,200
It's not easy for everyone.

443
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:08,490
That's why we need
to look out for each other.

444
00:17:08,490 --> 00:17:09,970
Don't you agree?

445
00:17:11,890 --> 00:17:12,680
I'll pocket it then.

446
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,160
Keep it.

447
00:17:14,349 --> 00:17:14,880
Take it.

448
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:18,099
Thanks, Boss.

449
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,050
What's going on today?

450
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:21,250
Everyone is so happy.

451
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:22,930
We're happy.

452
00:17:23,030 --> 00:17:24,030
Alright, I'm off.

453
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:24,920
Take care.

454
00:17:25,349 --> 00:17:26,510
Ride safe, Xiaoman.

455
00:17:26,510 --> 00:17:27,030
Okay.

456
00:17:29,270 --> 00:17:29,680
Uncle,

457
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,520
he won't find out, right?

458
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:32,920
It's fine. Let's go.

459
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,160
It's fine.

460
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,170
The gas tank Xiaoman got us is great.

461
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:39,110
The flame is bright blue.

462
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:40,680
Come on.

463
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,940
Isn't every newly filled tank like that?

464
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:45,400
You don't go into the kitchen,
what do you know?

465
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,030
It's just better than before.

466
00:17:47,030 --> 00:17:48,510
Yeah. There was...

467
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:49,680
There was a lot left inside.

468
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,740
I poured it all out.

469
00:17:52,350 --> 00:17:52,950
Let's eat.

470
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:53,720
Dig in.

471
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,510
Come on, try this beef.

472
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:56,710
-It’s tender.
-Okay.

473
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,400
You seem distracted.

474
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:02,550
Eat up.

475
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,640
Mr. Ding.

476
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:10,160
Didn't I just go to exchange the tank?

477
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,680
I found that the tanks
at that filling station

478
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:14,540
have a problem.

479
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,820
I lifted one while I was there.

480
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:18,680
Their empty tank

481
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,140
is much lighter than ours.

482
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:22,170
I think they tampered with it.

483
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:23,790
They must have added
something to the tank,

484
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,480
so it holds less gas.

485
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,620
And when I lifted the tank,

486
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:28,790
the boss's wife saw me.

487
00:18:28,790 --> 00:18:31,030
She slipped me 100 yuan

488
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:32,680
to keep my mouth shut.

489
00:18:33,590 --> 00:18:34,720
That's how it is now.

490
00:18:35,110 --> 00:18:37,260
Only crooked ways make money.

491
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:38,930
Mr. Ding,

492
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:42,370
I'm thinking of reporting them
to the Security Department.

493
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,550
Report them, right?

494
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:45,870
If not,

495
00:18:45,890 --> 00:18:46,830
it'll be our turn.

496
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:49,290
Since when do you
put soy sauce in dried tofu?

497
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,060
Is it too salty?

498
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:52,830
Yes.

499
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:54,880
Let's eat.

500
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,240
I'll go after the meal.

501
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:58,280
Xiaoman,

502
00:18:59,790 --> 00:19:00,830
what's the use?

503
00:19:02,070 --> 00:19:03,870
This happens at the factory too.

504
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,660
You can't fix everything.

505
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:16,270
Don't you need this job?

506
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:18,390
Just turn a blind eye.

507
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:28,400
The liquefied gas...

508
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,440
Xiaoman, what are you doing?

509
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,700
Why aren't you eating?

510
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:33,030
If the cylinder valve is loose,

511
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:33,400
or the seal isn't tight...

512
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,350
These chicken legs
my dad braised today are delicious.

513
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:36,640
Much better than before.

514
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:37,370
Come try one.

515
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:38,480
Save one for me.

516
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,210
It diffuses rapidly in the air,

517
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:41,640
mixes with the air,

518
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,350
and forms an explosive gas.

519
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:44,270
Xiaoman, is it that dangerous?

520
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:45,920
It's not that dangerous.

521
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,720
They just film it
like that to scare people.

522
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,160
I do this work every day.

523
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:52,480
Carrying that tank all over the streets,
nothing happens.

524
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:52,960
Here.

525
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:54,750
I've had a bite of this one.
Take the one underneath.

526
00:19:54,750 --> 00:19:55,920
It's really big.

527
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,510
Undermining the foundation of socialism.

528
00:19:58,510 --> 00:20:00,480
I'm telling you,
these chicken legs your dad made...

529
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,340
Not bad, right?

530
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:03,070
They're exploding with juice.

531
00:20:03,070 --> 00:20:05,720
For factory production
and residents' lives,

532
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,680
it poses a huge safety hazard.

533
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:10,070
It has caused multiple casualties

534
00:20:10,070 --> 00:20:11,270
and property damage.

535
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:13,030
To ensure safe production...

536
00:20:13,030 --> 00:20:15,090
Why put cilantro in the braised pork?

537
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:17,680
You eat it.

538
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:19,510
Okay, I'll eat it.

539
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,940
...strictly follow the rules
for using liquefied gas.

540
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,900
Why do you keep watching this?

541
00:20:28,350 --> 00:20:29,240
I'm just...

542
00:20:30,750 --> 00:20:31,550
taking a look.

543
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:33,490
Just taking a look.

544
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:37,790
I don't like watching
these fires and explosions.

545
00:20:37,790 --> 00:20:40,120
It's so scary
with all that blood and gore.

546
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:42,880
Stop watching. Turn it off.

547
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:43,550
Okay.

548
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:45,480
I'll turn it off.

549
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:52,310
Xiaoman.

550
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:55,240
How's that gas station you work at?

551
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,600
We can't do this anyway.

552
00:21:34,110 --> 00:21:34,750
Honey!

553
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,680
Open the door.

554
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:54,360
This...

555
00:21:54,930 --> 00:21:56,680
Is the pigsty not closed tight again?

556
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:57,210
The smell

557
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,110
is way too strong.

558
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:00,480
Uncle.

559
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:02,120
Let's stop raising them.

560
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:04,750
We deal with gas every day.

561
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:06,590
We rely on these pigs to cover the smell.

562
