I'm going then.

843
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:35,720
-Go.
-Come on! Come on!

844
00:32:35,750 --> 00:32:36,270
You'll nail it.

845
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:40,110
Good luck.

846
00:32:41,590 --> 00:32:42,790
It'll definitely work.

847
00:32:42,790 --> 00:32:43,640
As for Xiaodan,

848
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:45,640
didn't we see her hosting back then?

849
00:32:45,830 --> 00:32:46,760
She was amazing.

850
00:32:47,730 --> 00:32:49,790
Let me ask you something I shouldn't.

851
00:32:50,070 --> 00:32:52,330
Does her family know you brought her out?

852
00:32:52,970 --> 00:32:54,490
I left a note when we left.

853
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:56,080
They should know by now.

854
00:32:56,590 --> 00:32:57,920
You just left a note?

855
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,440
To put it lightly,

856
00:32:59,790 --> 00:33:00,750
it's a kidnapping.

857
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:02,030
To put it bluntly, you...

858
00:33:02,030 --> 00:33:03,830
You're holding her hostage, you know?

859
00:33:03,830 --> 00:33:05,160
What are you talking about?

860
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:06,880
What? Why would I abduct her?

861
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:09,440
If she even chips a tooth,
that counts as a minor injury.

862
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:10,600
You brought her out.

863
00:33:10,620 --> 00:33:11,820
You must be involved.

864
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:12,750
Oh my god.

865
00:33:13,260 --> 00:33:14,240
Don't let this thing with Xiaodan

866
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,500
get you thrown in jail.

867
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,790
Don't scare me like that.

868
00:33:17,790 --> 00:33:19,590
Why would I get myself thrown in jail?

869
00:33:19,590 --> 00:33:21,230
Liu is making it sound so serious.

870
00:33:21,230 --> 00:33:23,360
I'm not trying to scare you. It's true.

871
00:33:25,110 --> 00:33:25,790
Really?

872
00:33:26,070 --> 00:33:26,880
Use your head.

873
00:33:32,350 --> 00:33:32,830
Liu.

874
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,850
You said you'd give

875
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:37,270
some professional guidance,

876
00:33:37,750 --> 00:33:39,840
but you didn't offer anything useful.

877
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:42,100
You're just cramming at the last minute.

878
00:33:42,310 --> 00:33:44,110
Isn't it just for peace of mind?

879
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,440
Is that so?

880
00:33:48,750 --> 00:33:49,950
I studied for 5 years,

881
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:52,420
and I never even hosted the factory gala.

882
00:33:52,790 --> 00:33:53,960
Well, that tongue twist

883
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:54,820
is impressive.

884
00:33:56,270 --> 00:33:56,750
Right?

885
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,400
Your tongue is really...

886
00:33:58,480 --> 00:33:59,680
You're out. Xiaodan.

887
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:00,840
How was it?

888
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:04,070
How did it go? You passed, right?

889
00:34:04,510 --> 00:34:05,910
Are you acting right now?

890
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,640
Trying to surprise me later?

891
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:09,630
Is this a plot twist, Xiaodan?

892
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,570
Something's wrong.

893
00:34:12,230 --> 00:34:13,889
Looks like she didn't make it.

894
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:16,440
It's okay if you didn't pass.

895
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,710
Just treat it as fun.

896
00:34:18,030 --> 00:34:19,630
We just came out for a stroll.

897
00:34:19,670 --> 00:34:21,070
Not bad.

898
00:34:21,070 --> 00:34:21,840
Sorry for the trouble, Liu.

899
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:22,500
No problem.

900
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:24,440
I'm going to work. You guys carry on.

901
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,030
I'm off.

902
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:25,969
Xiaoman!

903
00:34:34,159 --> 00:34:35,690
Why are you running so fast?

904
00:34:38,150 --> 00:34:40,150
I've been chasing you the whole way.

905
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:51,900
Are you going to the restroom?

906
00:35:02,630 --> 00:35:03,430
What's wrong?

907
00:35:03,980 --> 00:35:05,060
You're asking me?

908
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,760
We agreed before we came.

909
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:11,470
Tiananmen, the Great Wall,
the Forbidden City, the Summer Palace.

910
00:35:11,470 --> 00:35:14,400
But since we got here,
we haven't been to a single one.

911
00:35:15,170 --> 00:35:15,760
Look.

912
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:17,240
Isn't this...

913
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:19,840
It's not that I won't go.

914
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:22,670
I'm just worried about you.

915
00:35:22,690 --> 00:35:23,820
Worried about what?

916
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,840
Sen said

917
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:28,050
that we're

918
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:31,440
not adults yet.

919
00:35:32,110 --> 00:35:33,960
I took you away,

920
00:35:34,190 --> 00:35:35,670
and we went so far.

921
00:35:35,920 --> 00:35:37,840
Our families must be worried.

922
00:35:38,190 --> 00:35:39,840
If I take you out again,

923
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:42,110
and something happens,

924
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:43,780
like you getting hurt...

925
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:46,510
The Gaokao is coming up.

926
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:49,410
I'm afraid if something happens,

927
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:51,570
I won't be able to explain it back home.

928
00:35:52,280 --> 00:35:53,880
Don't you have any regrets?

929
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:55,550
Regret what?

930
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:58,440
We went through all this trouble
and went nowhere.

931
00:35:58,440 --> 00:35:59,760
What do you mean we didn't make it?

932
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:01,220
Didn't we come to Beijing?

933
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:03,400
Didn't we participate in the competition?

934
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:05,460
It's their loss for not choosing you.

935
00:36:05,650 --> 00:36:07,760
At least you tried to pursue your dream.

936
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:09,880
Right? We won't regret trying.

937
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,530
Even if it seems like we didn't succeed,

938
00:36:11,530 --> 00:36:13,230
not trying at all
would be the real regret.

939
00:36:13,230 --> 00:36:15,090
What is there to be unhappy about?

940
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:20,150
True.

941
00:36:20,910 --> 00:36:22,400
You coming with me

942
00:36:23,190 --> 00:36:24,790
is the happiest thing for me.

943
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:26,980
We can come back later.

944
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:28,020
Right?

945
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:30,920
Anyway, we know the way now.

946
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,520
We know how to take the train.

947
00:36:32,580 --> 00:36:34,320
It'll be more convenient next time.

948
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:37,960
Let's just treat this as a scouting trip.

949
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:40,770
We'll come back after the exams.

950
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:41,290
Okay?

951
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:43,610
Don't be mad.

952
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:46,140
You scared me to death.

953
00:37:06,800 --> 00:37:07,510
We're back.

954
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,440
That was so fast. It feels like a dream.

955
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,440
It wasn't that far.

956
00:37:10,440 --> 00:37:12,190
We just sat for a bit and now we're back.

957
00:37:12,190 --> 00:37:13,650
We're back safe and sound.

958
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:16,590
My parents won't scold me, right?

959
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,040
Think about what to do when you get home.

960
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:22,710
I won't think about it.
I already went anyway.

961
00:37:27,490 --> 00:37:28,290
What's wrong?

962
00:37:29,500 --> 00:37:30,060
My dad.

963
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:41,960
Dad.

964
00:37:42,710 --> 00:37:44,840
How did you know I was on this train?

965
00:37:45,110 --> 00:37:46,710
There are only a few trains

966
00:37:46,710 --> 00:37:48,310
back from Beijing every day.

967
00:37:48,580 --> 00:37:49,510
So I just waited.

968
00:37:50,030 --> 00:37:50,890
I'm sorry, Dad.

969
00:37:51,110 --> 00:37:52,400
I made you worry.

970
00:37:53,230 --> 00:37:54,230
It's just...

971
00:37:54,230 --> 00:37:56,030
if I hadn't gone,

972
00:37:56,030 --> 00:37:58,090
I wouldn't have been able to let it go.

973
00:38:00,890 --> 00:38:02,020
You can let it go now?

974
00:38:10,810 --> 00:38:11,800
Let me carry it.

975
00:38:12,070 --> 00:38:13,470
Now that you can let it go,

976
00:38:13,980 --> 00:38:15,380
it's time to settle down.

977
00:38:15,760 --> 00:38:16,910
You know

978
00:38:17,010 --> 00:38:19,270
it's time to get down to business, right?

979
00:38:26,660 --> 00:38:27,390
Are you okay?

980
00:38:36,910 --> 00:38:38,710
Mrs. Ding, have you eaten?

981
00:38:39,630 --> 00:38:40,890
Xiaoman, you're back.

982
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,880
Nice accent.

983
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:47,210
Why are you saving all these underpants?

984
00:38:47,550 --> 00:38:49,110
Go check on Mr. Ding.

985
00:38:49,110 --> 00:38:50,310
He needs comforting.

986
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:51,210
Is he inside?

987
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:52,460
I'll go take a look.

988
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:53,880
Mr. Ding.

989
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:56,360
I bought you the Beijing Erguotou.

990
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:01,560
What's going on?

991
00:39:02,030 --> 00:39:02,590
Mr. Ding.

992
00:39:02,610 --> 00:39:03,460
I'm fine.

993
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,470
What are you doing?

994
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:07,380
Put it in the wine cabinet.

995
00:39:07,510 --> 00:39:09,110
Well, what's wrong?

996
00:39:09,370 --> 00:39:10,710
Why are you using a hot water bottle?

997
00:39:10,710 --> 00:39:11,630
It's nothing.

998
00:39:11,630 --> 00:39:12,360
What do you mean nothing?

999
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:14,360
He has had the runs since last night.

1000
00:39:14,670 --> 00:39:15,730
His legs are jelly.

1001
00:39:16,110 --> 00:39:18,150
He's so big. I can't handle him.

1002
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:19,370
Oh my god.

1003
00:39:19,370 --> 00:39:20,070
You don't look good.

1004
00:39:20,070 --> 00:39:21,070
Hurry up.

1005
00:39:21,070 --> 00:39:21,920
Let me take you to the hospital.

1006
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:22,760
All right, forget it.

1007
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:23,550
Forget it.

1008
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:26,740
You'll let them make all the money off us.

1009
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:28,400
Besides, I've emptied my bowels.

1010
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:29,800
If they want a stool sample or something,

1011
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,710
what am I supposed to give them?
There's nothing left.

1012
00:39:31,710 --> 00:39:33,550
Didn't you say being empty is good?

1013
00:39:33,550 --> 00:39:35,610
Saves you from soiling the mattress.

1014
00:39:36,030 --> 00:39:37,630
Why are you getting so nasty?

1015
00:39:38,110 --> 00:39:39,550
Well, what kind of nasty stuff did you eat

1016
00:39:39,550 --> 00:39:40,920
to end up with the runs like this?

1017
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,550
Never mind that.
Put it in the liquor cabinet.

1018
00:39:42,550 --> 00:39:43,710
Hurry. Come to the hospital with me now.

1019
00:39:43,710 --> 00:39:44,700
Don't stay at home.

1020
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:45,490
Let's go.

1021
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:46,330
Xiaoman.

1022
00:39:47,110 --> 00:39:47,710
Make way.

1023
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:48,280
What?

1024
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:49,110
Make way for me. Quick.

1025
00:39:49,110 --> 00:39:49,880
Who is it?

1026
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:55,030
Put... Put your shoes on.

1027
00:39:55,030 --> 00:39:55,880
Bring me my slippers.

1028
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:57,880
Shoes, shoes, shoes. Here they are.

1029
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:01,570
How did it go?

1030
00:40:04,190 --> 00:40:05,920
The supplier isn't answering.

1031
00:40:07,200 --> 00:40:08,030
Don't worry.

1032
00:40:08,050 --> 00:40:08,780
Don't panic.

1033
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:11,800
Let's take back
everything we gifted or sold,

1034
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:13,000
and recall it all.

1035
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:14,630
Full refund.

1036
00:40:15,200 --> 00:40:17,360
No, but we can't just say

1037
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,480
it's the royal jelly's fault yet.

1038
00:40:19,510 --> 00:40:20,920
Honey, let's be sure first.

1039
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,550
If it's not the royal jelly,

1040
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:24,630
we'll keep selling it.

1041
00:40:24,630 --> 00:40:25,900
But if it really is the royal jelly,

1042
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:27,430
aren't we scamming people?

1043
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:30,440
Who is it?

1044
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:31,590
Third Aunt.

1045
00:40:31,630 --> 00:40:32,550
Coming.

1046
00:40:34,670 --> 00:40:35,400
Third Aunt,

1047
00:40:35,400 --> 00:40:36,500
what brings you here?

1048
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:38,390
W-W-What's wrong?

1049
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:41,320
Third Aunt.

1050
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:44,320
Xia Lei's mom.

1051
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:45,920
You need to give me

1052
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:47,580
a refund for this royal jelly.

1053
00:40:47,710 --> 00:40:48,190
Well...

1054
00:40:48,360 --> 00:40:50,030
I've heard from so many people,

1055
00:40:50,030 --> 00:40:52,230
drinking this stuff gives you diarrhea.

1056
00:40:52,230 --> 00:40:55,080
Third Aunt, it might
not be the royal jelly.

1057
00:40:55,110 --> 00:40:57,670
It could be... with some other food...

1058
00:40:57,670 --> 00:40:58,670
Did it clash?

1059
00:40:58,670 --> 00:41:00,070
Or cause a reaction?

1060
00:41:00,230 --> 00:41:00,880
Yes.

1061
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:01,920
Then tell me.

1062
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:04,320
What food does your royal jelly

1063
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,550
clash with or react to?

1064
00:41:05,550 --> 00:41:06,840
Is it persimmons?

1065
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,000
Or tangerines?

1066
00:41:08,030 --> 00:41:10,480
Third Aunt, let's not discuss this now.

1067
00:41:11,230 --> 00:41:12,690
We'll refund everything.

1068
00:41:12,690 --> 00:41:13,690
-We'll return them by box.
-No.

1069
00:41:13,690 --> 00:41:14,820
We'll refund it all.

1070
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,670
All my money is tied up in royal jelly.

1071
00:41:17,690 --> 00:41:18,230
-Well…
-I know.

1072
00:41:18,230 --> 00:41:19,440
But payday isn't until next month.

1073
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,440
I know.

1074
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:22,640
I've got you covered.

1075
00:41:22,920 --> 00:41:23,650
Don't worry.

1076
00:41:24,550 --> 00:41:26,710
Auntie, don't worry. I'll refund you.

1077
00:41:35,550 --> 00:41:36,360
Don't look.

1078
00:41:44,480 --> 00:41:45,070
Auntie.

1079
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:46,400
200.

1080
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:49,090
I've refunded you everything.

1081
00:41:56,610 --> 00:41:58,780
I drank a few bottles.

1082
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,920
It's fine. No deduction.
I'll refund the whole box.

1083
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,400
You actually wanted to deduct money?

1084
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:03,610
No, no, no. That's not what I meant.

1085
00:42:03,610 --> 00:42:04,570
Let me tell you,

1086
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:07,000
if my old man gets diarrhea,

1087
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:08,110
you have to take responsibility.

1088
00:42:08,110 --> 00:42:10,440
We will. We'll take full responsibility.

1089
00:42:10,630 --> 00:42:12,230
You can go with peace of mind.

1090
00:42:12,630 --> 00:42:14,360
I won't see you out, Third Aunt.

1091
00:42:16,960 --> 00:42:18,360
She's got quite a temper.

1092
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,360
Nice private stash.

1093
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:22,760
You've saved quite a lot.

1094
00:42:23,670 --> 00:42:24,190
This...

1095
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:27,740
...doesn't spoil your joy
of redistributing the wealth, does it?

1096
00:42:27,740 --> 00:42:28,300
Here.

1097
00:42:29,690 --> 00:42:30,370
Not at all.

1098
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:31,760
That's good.

1099
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:40,630
I just wanted to save
some living expenses for Xia Lei.

1100
00:42:40,630 --> 00:42:41,760
I just want him to...

1101
00:42:42,030 --> 00:42:43,630
...have some tuition money.

1102
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:45,360
What a mess this is.

1103
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,590
I know.

1104
00:42:47,030 --> 00:42:48,490
Alright. It's in the past.

1105
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:49,960
It's okay.

1106
00:42:50,490 --> 00:42:51,070
Yeah.

1107
00:42:51,070 --> 00:42:52,400
How does that saying go?

1108
00:42:53,190 --> 00:42:56,280
The strong pass is like a wall of iron.

1109
00:42:57,760 --> 00:43:01,400
But now we step forward from the start.

1110
00:43:01,860 --> 00:43:03,320
Alright. That's the only phrase I learned.

1111
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,440
I finally got to use it today.
